SKILL|hermes-agent-skill-authoring|"Author in-repo SKILL.md: frontmatter, validator, structure."
STEP|1|**User-local:** `~/.hermes/skills/<maybe-category>/<name>/SKILL.md` â€” personal, not shared. Created via `skill_manage(action='create')`.
STEP|2|**In-repo (this skill is about this case):** `/home/bb/hermes-agent/skills/<category>/<name>/SKILL.md` â€” committed, shipped with the package. Use `write_file` + `git add`. `skill_manage(action='create
STEP|3|User asks you to add a skill "in this branch / repo / commit"
STEP|4|You're committing a reusable workflow that should ship with hermes-agent
STEP|5|You're editing an existing skill under `/home/bb/hermes-agent/skills/` (use `patch` for small edits, `write_file` for rewrites; `skill_manage` still works for patch on in-repo skills, but not for `cre
STEP|6|Starts with `---` as the first bytes (no leading blank line).
STEP|7|Closes with `\n---\n` before the body.
STEP|8|Parses as a YAML mapping.
STEP|9|`name` field present.
STEP|10|`description` field present, â‰¤ **1024 chars** (`MAX_DESCRIPTION_LENGTH`).
STEP|11|Non-empty body after the closing `---`.
STEP|12|Description: â‰¤ 1024 chars (enforced).
STEP|13|Full SKILL.md: â‰¤ 100,000 chars (enforced as `MAX_SKILL_CONTENT_CHARS`, ~36k tokens).
STEP|14|Peer skills in `software-development/` sit at **8-14k chars**. Aim for that range. If you're pushing past 20k, split into `references/*.md` and reference them from SKILL.md.
STEP|15|Bulleted triggers
STEP|16|"Don't use for:" counter-triggers
STEP|17|Quick-reference tables are common
STEP|18|Code blocks with exact commands
STEP|19|Hermes-specific recipes (tests via scripts/run_tests.sh, ui-tui paths, etc.)
STEP|20|[ ] Checkbox list of post-action verifications
STEP|21|**Survey peers** in the target category:
STEP|22|**Check validator constraints** in `tools/skill_manager_tool.py` if unsure.
STEP|23|**Draft** with `write_file` to `skills/<category>/<name>/SKILL.md`.
STEP|24|**Validate locally**:
STEP|25|**Git add + commit** on the active branch.
STEP|26|**Note:** the CURRENT session's skill loader is cached â€” `skill_view` / `skills_list` will not see the new skill until a new session. This is expected, not a bug.
STEP|27|**Small fix (typo, added pitfall, tightened trigger):** `skill_manage(action='patch', name=..., old_string=..., new_string=...)` works fine on in-repo skills.
STEP|28|**Major rewrite:** `write_file` the whole SKILL.md. `skill_manage(action='edit')` also works but requires supplying the full new content.
STEP|29|**Adding supporting files:** `write_file` to `skills/<category>/<name>/references/<file>.md`, `templates/<file>`, or `scripts/<file>`. `skill_manage(action='write_file')` also works and enforces the r
STEP|30|**Always commit** the edit â€” in-repo skills are source, not runtime state.
STEP|31|**Using `skill_manage(action='create')` for an in-repo skill.** It writes to `~/.hermes/skills/`, not the repo tree. Use `write_file` for in-repo creation.
STEP|32|**Leading whitespace before `---`.** The validator checks `content.startswith("---")`; any leading blank line or BOM fails validation.
STEP|33|**Description too generic.** Peer descriptions start with "Use when ..." and describe the *trigger class*, not the one task. "Use when debugging X" > "Debug X".
STEP|34|**Forgetting the author/license/metadata block.** Not validator-enforced, but every peer has it; omitting makes the skill look half-finished.
STEP|35|**Writing a skill that duplicates a peer.** Before creating, `ls skills/<category>/` and open 2-3 peers. Prefer extending an existing skill to creating a narrow sibling.
STEP|36|**Expecting the current session to see the new skill.** It won't. The skill loader is initialized at session start. Verify in a fresh session or via `skill_view` using the exact path.
STEP|37|**Linking to skills that don't exist in-repo.** `related_skills: [some-user-local-skill]` works for you but breaks for other clones. Prefer only in-repo links.
STEP|38|[ ] File is at `skills/<category>/<name>/SKILL.md` (not in `~/.hermes/skills/`)
STEP|39|[ ] Frontmatter starts at byte 0 with `---`, closes with `\n---\n`
STEP|40|[ ] `name`, `description`, `version`, `author`, `license`, `metadata.hermes.{tags, related_skills}` all present
STEP|41|[ ] Name â‰¤ 64 chars, lowercase + hyphens
STEP|42|[ ] Description â‰¤ 1024 chars and starts with "Use when ..."
STEP|43|[ ] Total file â‰¤ 100,000 chars (aim for 8-15k)
STEP|44|[ ] Structure: `# Title` â†’ `## Overview` â†’ `## When to Use` â†’ body â†’ `## Common Pitfalls` â†’ `## Verification Checklist`
STEP|45|[ ] `related_skills` references resolve in-repo (or are explicitly OK to be user-local)
STEP|46|[ ] `git add skills/<category>/<name>/ && git commit` completed on the intended branch
